Port the inline tombstone system from Go beads to beads-rs.

## Problem

When issues are deleted, we need to:
1. Preserve delete markers for sync (CRDT tombstones)
2. Support 3-way merge of deletions
3. Eventually garbage collect old tombstones
4. Keep dependency graph intact during TTL period

## Go beads approach

Deleted issues become tombstones with:
- `deleted_at`: Timestamp of deletion
- `deleted_by`: Actor who deleted
- `delete_reason`: Why deleted
- `original_type`: Issue type before deletion

Tombstones are:
- Inline in issues table (not separate deletions.jsonl)
- Exported to JSONL like normal issues
- Pruned after TTL (default 30 days)
- Kept if open issues still depend on them

## Implementation approach

**Schema changes** (`src/storage/schema.sql`):
```sql
ALTER TABLE issues ADD COLUMN deleted_at DATETIME;
ALTER TABLE issues ADD COLUMN deleted_by TEXT DEFAULT '';
ALTER TABLE issues ADD COLUMN delete_reason TEXT DEFAULT '';
ALTER TABLE issues ADD COLUMN original_type TEXT DEFAULT '';

-- Partial index for efficient TTL queries
CREATE INDEX idx_issues_deleted_at 
    ON issues(deleted_at) 
    WHERE deleted_at IS NOT NULL;
```

**Core types** (`src/core/types.rs`):
```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
pub struct Issue {
    pub id: String,
    pub title: String,
    pub status: Status,
    // ... other fields ...

    // Tombstone fields
    pub deleted_at: Option<DateTime<Utc>>,
    pub deleted_by: Option<String>,
    pub delete_reason: Option<String>,
    pub original_type: Option<IssueType>,
}

impl Issue {
    /// Check if issue is a tombstone
    pub fn is_tombstone(&self) -> bool {
        self.deleted_at.is_some()
    }

    /// Check if tombstone is expired (past TTL)
    pub fn is_expired(&self, ttl: Duration) -> bool {
        if let Some(deleted_at) = self.deleted_at {
            Utc::now() - deleted_at > ttl
        } else {
            false
        }
    }
}

/// Default tombstone TTL
pub const DEFAULT_TOMBSTONE_TTL: Duration = Duration::days(30);

/// Minimum tombstone TTL for safety
pub const MIN_TOMBSTONE_TTL: Duration = Duration::days(7);
```

**Delete operation** (`src/daemon/operations.rs`):
```rust
pub fn delete_issue(
    state: &mut CanonicalState,
    issue_id: &str,
    actor: &str,
    reason: Option<&str>,
) -> Result<()> {
    let mut issue = state.get_issue_mut(issue_id)?;

    // Convert to tombstone
    issue.deleted_at = Some(Utc::now());
    issue.deleted_by = Some(actor.to_string());
    issue.delete_reason = reason.map(|s| s.to_string());
    issue.original_type = Some(issue.issue_type.clone());

    // Mark dirty for export
    state.mark_dirty(issue_id);

    Ok(())
}
```

**Tombstone pruning** (`src/daemon/compact.rs`):
```rust
/// Prune expired tombstones that have no open dependencies
pub fn prune_tombstones(
    state: &mut CanonicalState,
    ttl: Duration,
) -> Result<PruneResult> {
    let mut result = PruneResult::default();

    // Find expired tombstones
    let expired: Vec<_> = state.issues()
        .filter(|i| i.is_expired(ttl))
        .map(|i| i.id.clone())
        .collect();

    // Build dependency map: tombstone_id -> [dependent_issue_ids]
    let deps_map = build_reverse_deps(state);

    // Only prune tombstones with no open dependents
    for tombstone_id in expired {
        if let Some(dependents) = deps_map.get(&tombstone_id) {
            let has_open_deps = dependents.iter()
                .any(|dep_id| {
                    state.get_issue(dep_id)
                        .map(|i| i.status == Status::Open)
                        .unwrap_or(false)
                });

            if has_open_deps {
                result.kept.push(tombstone_id.clone());
                continue;
            }
        }

        // Safe to delete
        state.remove_issue(&tombstone_id)?;
        result.deleted.push(tombstone_id);
    }

    Ok(result)
}

#[derive(Debug, Default)]
pub struct PruneResult {
    pub deleted: Vec<String>,
    pub kept: Vec<String>,
}
```

